HEADWORD: Abruptly
<hw>Ab*rupt"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In an abrupt
manner; without giving notice, or without the usual forms;
suddenly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Precipitously.</def>⟦br⟧
